      "writtenOn": "2020-05-01T18:10:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I didn\u0027t notice this the first time, but this could be potentially dangerous. array is declared on the stack, not the heap. So when this function returns we are pointing to an old stackframe.\n\nI think a better solution is to mimic what we do for getTotalMatrix, where the client allocates memory, passes the pointer into getColor and then frees it after copying it into a typed array.",
